, our best-fitting cases\nsuggest that the projectile responsible for the Dichotomy-forming event was of\nradius 500-750 km, and collided with Mars at an impact angle of 15-30{\\deg}\nwith a velocity of 1.2-1.4 times mutual escape speed ($\\sim$6-7 km/s).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Dec 2022 18:20:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-08"}
