ver all plain\nevaluators as fixed-points by instantiation. We introduce a systematic notation\nfor both evaluator styles and use it to summarise strategy and evaluator\nequivalences, including (non-)equivalences within a style and\n(non-)equivalences between styles not proven by the transformation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Dec 2022 18:56:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2022 13:22:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-07"}
