other techniques ever proposed for calculations of\nthe DM interactions. Particularly, we argue that the spin-current model for the\nDM interactions can be derived from the MFT based expression and is the\nrelativistic counterpart of the double exchange, occurring in metallic systems\nin the limit of infinite exchange splitting.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2022 07:57:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Feb 2023 04:19:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-02"}
