m by de-Ockhamization does not\nrequire any constraints at all, first-class or second-class, because any\ndynamical variable in any Lagrangian can be de-Ockhamized into exhibiting\ntrivial additive artificial gauge freedom by splitting one quantity into the\nsum of two. Physically interesting gauge freedom, however, is typically\ngenerated by a tuned sum of first-class constraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2022 12:57:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-07"}
